The enemy, wrought up to the highest pitch of courage by the leader’s example and exhortation‚ occupies a carefully chosen position, strong by nature, and additionally strengthened by stone walls, which are carried by the Roman ‘ testudo ’ ; a second position further up the heights is stormed with equal success3 the close attack of the legions, added to the storm of missiles hurled by the light troops on the bare heads and unprotected bodies of their adversaries, completing the victory and carnage. The immediate capture of the wife and daughter, and surrender of the brothers of Caratacus,⁷ is followed soon by his own deliverance into captivity‚ and from the time of the transportation of these illustrious prisoners to Rome ⁸ the great house of Cunobelinus is lost sight of in British history!
